When a new user signs up, they see a message about successful signup. In the {{atlassian-jira/WEB-INF/classes/com/atlassian/jira/web/action/JiraWebActionSupport.properties}} file, the message is:

{code}
signup.success = You have successfully signed up. If you forget your password, you can have it emailed to you.
{code}

This seems inaccurate though, as the password itself isn't mailed, but a password reset link is emailed. Some users are sensitive to [passwords themselves being emailed in the clear|https://twitter.com/plexus/status/412592881744871425]. Perhaps the message should say:

{code}
signup.success = You have successfully signed up. If you forget your password, you can request a password reset link be emailed to you.
{code}

Or similar.

